import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median Age: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the victims?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="gender", data=data, palette="Set2")
    ax.set(xlabel='Gender', ylabel='Count')
    ax.axhline(y=data['gender'].value_counts(normalize=True)['Male']*100, color='r', linestyle='--', label='Male: {:.2f}%'.format(data['gender'].value_counts(normalize=True)['Male']*100))
    ax.axhline(y=data['gender'].value_counts(normalize=True)['Female']*100, color='g', linestyle='--', label='Female: {:.2f}%'.format(data['gender'].value_counts(normalize=True)['Female']*100))
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data = data[data['type'].isin(['Death', 'Not riot-related'])]
    data = data.groupby('type').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.pie(data['counts'], labels=data['type'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=['#ff7f0e', '#1f77b4'])
    ax.axis('equal')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of deaths by type?')
    ax.legend(title='Type', loc='best', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['death_date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['death_date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['death_date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.scatterplot(x='longitude', y='latitude', data=data, hue='type', ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the geographical distribution of the deaths?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Type', loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
